From: Shengjing Zhu <zhsj@debian.org>
Date: Sun, 28 Jul 2024 19:44:27 -0400
Subject: Use system-installed googletest via CMake package discovery

Rebased for opencc 1.4.1: the ENABLE_GTEST block gained a bundled-source
existence check ahead of the USE_SYSTEM_GTEST branch since 1.4.0 (source
package profiles may strip deps/googletest), shifting this hunk's
context; only the if/else/endif around add_subdirectory is touched here.

Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-07-11
---
--- OpenCC.orig/CMakeLists.txt
+++ OpenCC/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -395,6 +395,8 @@
   endif()
   if(NOT USE_SYSTEM_GTEST)
     add_subdirectory(deps/googletest-1.15.0)
+  else()
+    find_package(GTest CONFIG REQUIRED)
   endif()
   enable_testing()
 endif()
